      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "Why did BERT sometimes leave selected tokens unchanged or replace them randomly instead of always using a mask token?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "To make the model build useful contextual representations even when explicit mask tokens are absent at test time.",
        "To prevent the model from learning subword embeddings.",
        "To make every sentence exactly the same length.",
        "To convert the encoder into a left-to-right decoder."
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "If training only used artificial mask symbols, the model could rely too much on a pattern that does not appear in ordinary downstream inputs. Random and unchanged cases make training closer to real use.",
